It is illegal to import alcohol without a licence. It is also illegal to drink alcohol in a public place. The main religion on Pitcairn is Seventh Day Adventism. Sabbath is observed on Saturday. The import of honey is forbidden, and the import of of plant and animal products is strictly controlled; visitors should contact the Pitcairn Islands Office in Auckland for advice before travelling.
Same sex marriage has been legal in the Pitcairn Islands since 2015.
